.TH zanna 7 "Zanna" "Project overview" "Miscellanea"
.SH NAME
zanna \- overview of the Zanna toolchain, frontends, and runtime
.SH DESCRIPTION
Zanna is a modular language and runtime stack built around Zanna IL.
.IP \(bu 2
Frontends include Zia and Zanna BASIC.
.IP \(bu 2
The VM executes textual IL and frontend-generated programs.
.IP \(bu 2
Native backends emit executables for supported targets.
.IP \(bu 2
The runtime library exposes the \fBZanna.*\fR namespace used by both frontends.
.PP
The main workflow is through \fBzanna\fR(1): build or run a \fC.zia\fR file,
\fC.bas\fR file, project directory, or \fCzanna.project\fR.
.SH COMMON TOOLS
.TP
\fBzanna\fR(1)
Project driver for Zia, BASIC, IL, native builds, REPL, and packaging.
.TP
\fBzia\fR(1)
Single-file Zia driver.
.TP
\fBvbasic\fR(1)
Single-file BASIC driver.
.TP
\fBilrun\fR(1)
Simple textual IL runner.
.TP
\fBil-verify\fR(1)
IL verifier.
.TP
\fBil-dis\fR(1)
IL-to-bytecode disassembler.
.TP
\fBbasic-ast-dump\fR(1), \fBbasic-lex-dump\fR(1)
Developer utilities for BASIC parsing and lexing.
.SH FILES
Textual IL files typically end with \fC.il\fR.
.PP
Zia source files typically end with \fC.zia\fR.
.PP
BASIC source files typically end with \fC.bas\fR.
.PP
Project roots may contain a \fCzanna.project\fR file.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBzanna\fR(1), \fBzia\fR(1), \fBvbasic\fR(1), \fBilrun\fR(1), \fBil-verify\fR(1), \fBil-dis\fR(1)
